Chapter: Cite Fn Call

 Probe sample for ONEFOREWORD (docs/Active/Compiler/ONEFOREWORD.md).

 `to-unicode` is defined in foreword/CCE.codex and is NOT in
 sorted-builtin-names, so unlike is-letter/is-digit/is-whitespace it is
 not inlined by either compiler's builtin dispatch. Its use here
 exercises the real cross-project-function-emission path.

 Observed failure mode today (Codex.Cli build):
   - codex build samples/cite-fn-call.codex succeeds silently and emits
     samples/cite-fn-call.cs.
   - The generated C# calls `to_unicode(13L)` but never defines it.
   - `dotnet build` on the output fails with CS0103 on that reference.
   - The type `CharClass` and runtime `_Cce` preamble ARE emitted from
     the cited chapter; only function bodies are skipped.

 When Step 2 of ONEFOREWORD lands (cross-project function emission in
 codex-cli), this sample compiles and prints 101 on both paths. Until
 then it is the acceptance test for the feature.

  cites Foreword chapter CCE

Section: Definitions

  main : [Console] Nothing = act
    print-line ("to-unicode 13 = " ++ show (to-unicode 13))
  end

